rxdo.6 KEY DESIGN (bead wins on conflict):
- `from query-definition:` re-evaluates; `from query-run:` uses its
  retained relation (TYPED error if not retained); `from result-set:` uses
  the stored relation; `from cohort:` re-evaluates (dynamic) or yields
  members (snapshot). All usable as set-algebra operands.
- @name STAYS macro-expansion for dynamic saved queries — do NOT overload
  it for results (freshness surprise is the named anti-goal).
- References lower to a typed RefOperand AST node — NEVER textual
  expansion — so `explain` shows parent query/run/result lineage and
  query_edges emit from the planner.
- LALR PITFALL (from bd memory, verbatim): any new terminal containing a
  colon must slot ABOVE FIELD_CLAUSE.4 priority or it is eaten as a field
  clause. Pipeline stages are hand-parsed outside the grammar — check the
  expression.py stage splitter FIRST; from-stage may need no grammar
  change at all.
- Grain typing: RefOperand carries the referenced relation's grain;
  mixed-grain composition FAILS CLOSED with a suggestion (set-algebra
  doctrine). Cycle guard: planner detects ref cycles across query_edges +
  macro expansion depth before materialization.

rxdo.5 KEY DESIGN (bead wins on conflict):
- Fourth default convergence stage (after fts/embed/insights) using the
  EXISTING session-scoped stage hooks — check_sessions/execute_sessions +
  false_means_pending; the bead verified ConvergenceStage already supports
  this with NO engine changes. Do not modify the converger engine.
- A watched query (query_names.watch=1) re-materializes when member
  sessions change; membership-merkle comparison emits ONE query-delta
  FINDING candidate (never active, never inject) citing old+new
  result-set refs.
- Dedup by STABLE FINDING IDENTITY, not events: same content-hash → same
  finding id → already present → a re-ingest storm is STRUCTURALLY
  incapable of re-notifying. Baseline-then-notify. Self-trigger firewall:
  standing queries exclude their own scope_ref and notice.* events by
  default (recursive-loop guard).
- Index-reset false-drift guard: cache-only result sets cannot produce
  deltas after reset; only user.db-pinned baselines compare.
- Findings-as-tests: a PROMOTED finding with value.expected re-runs and
  emits a finding-drift candidate TARGETING the original on divergence —
  drift findings are new claims awaiting judgment, never mutations of the
  original.
- check_sessions maps changed sessions to affected watched queries via
  scoped predicate fingerprints — global corpus epoch first; scoped-epoch
  fast-follow is OUT of this slice (note it as follow-up).

